:7:\"banners\";a:2:{s:3:\"low\";s:61:\"https://ps.w.org/bbpress/assets/banner-772x250.png?rev=478663\";s:4:\"high\";s:62:\"https://ps.w.org/bbpress/assets/banner-1544x500.png?rev=567403\";}}s:14:\"contact-form-7\";a:25:{s:4:\"name\";s:14:\"Contact Form 7\";s:4:\"slug\";s:14:\"contact-form-7\";s:7:\"version\";s:3:\"5.4\";s:6:\"author\";s:62:\"<a href=\"https://ideasilo.wordpress.com/\">Takayuki Miyoshi</a>\";s:14:\"author_profile\";s:43:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/takayukister\";s:12:\"contributors\";a:1:{s:12:\"takayukister\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:43:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/takayukister\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:88:\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/bb7bc21850c77e9eb16b44102f4a539d?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:16:\"Takayuki Miyoshi\";}}s:8:\"requires\";s:3:\"5.5\";s:6:\"tested\";s:3:\"5.7\";s:12:\"requires_php\";b:0;s:6:\"rating\";i:82;s:7:\"ratings\";a:5:{i:5;i:1304;i:4;i:131;i:3;i:56;i:2;i:49;i:1;i:315;}s:11:\"num_ratings\";i:1855;s:15:\"support_threads\";i:556;s:24:\"support_threads_resolved\";i:183;s:15:\"active_installs\";i:5000000;s:12:\"last_updated\";s:22:\"2021-02-24 12:24pm GMT\";s:5:\"added\";s:10:\"2007-08-02\";s:8:\"homepage\";s:25:\"https://contactform7.com/\";s:8:\"sections\";a:6:{s:11:\"description\";s:2974:\"<p>Contact Form 7 can manage multiple contact forms, plus you can customize the form and the mail contents flexibly with simple markup. The form supports Ajax-powered submitting, CAPTCHA, Akismet spam filtering and so on.</p>\n<h4>Docs and support</h4>\n<p>You can find <a href=\"https://contactform7.com/docs/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">docs</a>, <a href=\"https://contactform7.com/faq/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">FAQ</a> and more detailed information about Contact Form 7 on <a href=\"https://contactform7.com/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">contactform7.com</a>. When you can&#8217;t find the answer to your question on the FAQ or in any of the documentation, check the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/contact-form-7/\">support forum</a> on WordPress.org. If you can&#8217;t locate any topics that pertain to your particular issue, post a new topic for it.</p>\n<h4>Contact Form 7 needs your support</h4>\n<p>It is hard to continue development and support for this free plugin without contributions from users like you. If you enjoy using Contact Form 7 and find it useful, please consider <a href=\"https://contactform7.com/donate/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">making a donation</a>. Your donation will help encourage and support the plugin&#8217;s continued development and better user support.</p>\n<h4>Privacy notices</h4>\n<p>With the default configuration, this plugin, in itself, does not:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>track users by stealth;</li>\n<li>write any user personal data to the database;</li>\n<li>send any data to external servers;</li>\n<li>use cookies.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you activate certain features in this plugin, the contact form submitter&#8217;s personal data, including their IP address, may be sent to the service provider. Thus, confirming the provider&#8217;s privacy policy is recommended. These features include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>reCAPTCHA (<a href=\"https://policies.google.com/?hl=en\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Google</a>)</li>\n<li>Akismet (<a href=\"https://automattic.com/privacy/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Automattic</a>)</li>\n<li>Constant Contact (<a href=\"https://www.endurance.com/privacy\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Endurance International Group</a>)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.sendinblue.com/legal/privacypolicy/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Sendinblue</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Recommended plugins</h4>\n<p>The following plugins are recommended for Contact Form 7 users:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/flamingo/\">Flamingo</a> by Takayuki Miyoshi &#8211; With Flamingo, you can save submitted messages via contact forms in the database.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/bogo/\">Bogo</a> by Takayuki Miyoshi &#8211; Bogo is a straight-forward multilingual plugin that doesn&#8217;t cause headaches.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Translations</h4>\n<p>You can <a href=\"https://contactform7.com/translating-contact-form-7/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">translate Contact Form 7</a> on <a href=\"https://translate.wordpress.org/projects/wp-plugins/contact-form-7\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">translate.wordpress.org</a>.</p>\n\";s:12:\"installation\";s:458:\"<ol>\n<li>Upload the entire <code>contact-form-7</code> folder to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory.</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the <strong>Plugins</strong> screen (<strong>Plugins &gt; Installed Plugins</strong>).</li>\n</ol>\n<p>You will find <strong>Contact</strong> menu in your WordPress admin screen.</p>\n<p>For basic usage, have a look at the <a href=\"https://contactform7.com/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">plugin&#8217;s website</a>.</p>\n\";s:3:\"faq\";s:439:\"<p>Do you have questions or issues with Contact Form 7? Use these support channels appropriately.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://contactform7.com/docs/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Docs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://contactform7.com/faq/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">FAQ</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/contact-form-7/\">Support forum</a></li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"https://contactform7.com/support/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Support</a></p>\n\";s:9:\"changelog\";s:184:\"<p>For more information, see <a href=\"https://contactform7.com/category/releases/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Releases</a>.</p>\n<h4>5.4</h4>\n<p>https://contactform7.com/contact-form-7-54/</p>\n\";s:11:\"screenshots\";s:225:\"<ol><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/contact-form-7/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=1176454\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/contact-form-7/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=1176454\" alt=\"screenshot-1.png\"></a><p>screenshot-1.png</p></li></ol>\";s:7:\"reviews\";s:16280:\"<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">whel is spinning and spinning</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/taufrisch88\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/da6955a1eb485e6f0a1cb05f36b082da?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/da6955a1eb485e6f0a1cb05f36b082da?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/taufrisch88\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Hans <small>(taufrisch88)</small></a> on <span class=\"review-date\">March 1, 2021</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">wheel is spinning and spinning.\nDO I have to change the form plugin for 15 websites now??</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Powerful but not stable</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"2 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"2\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kreanuts\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e8515fe0d8ee168a53206e9c09746d94?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e8515fe0d8ee168a53206e9c09746d94?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kreanuts\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Killian Leroux <small>(KreaNuts)</small></a> on <span class=\"review-date\">March 1, 2021</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">CF7 is a powerful plugin, I use it since many years, but I regret his unstable side: after each update, I fear bugs, I have to verify the plugin is always usable and it isn\'t always the case :/\nFor example with this last update (5.3.2 &gt; 5.4), a message \"Uploading a file fails for any reason\" appears but... The submit has no error :/\nSo I\'m looking for a better plugin or other solution... :\'(</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Fix the last update you released</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/123nadav\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/425612cca97348fe83f8bb25bbc1feb8?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/425612cca97348fe83f8bb25bbc1feb8?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/123nadav\" class=\"reviewer-name\">123nadav</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">March 1, 2021</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Fix your last update, dont ignore people, help them.\nYou have 5 million users with problems from your last update and you refuse to fix it.\nmore than 50 people complained, if you notice here, you got 7 bad reviews in February.\n\nThis because you refuse to fix your update.\nyou must fix it.\n\nI promise you if you will fix it a lot of people will remove their bad reviews.\nINCLUDING ME.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">No support at all</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/nevaha\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/78427bcfcb032a844d6dbf612bceeac0?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/78427bcfcb032a844d6dbf612bceeac0?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/nevaha\" class=\"reviewer-name\">nevaha</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">February 28, 2021</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Sorry @takayukister - Time to move to another plugin...</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">5.4 breaks my Homepage completety</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/aedon\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/96d63c487f424402e62d64a3179a9a07?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/96d63c487f424402e62d64a3179a9a07?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/aedon\" class=\"reviewer-name\">aedon</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">February 28, 2021</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Even my intro won*t start with 5.4 enabled! Reverted to Version 5.3.2, which works completely flawless. What a crap. Please fix it.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Very Poor Support</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/lesbell\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/3584e8390f4c2a6e5712bb61d394bd64?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/3584e8390f4c2a6e5712bb61d394bd64?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/lesbell\" class=\"reviewer-name\">lesbell</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">February 26, 2021</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I\'ve used this plugin for many years on many sites without any problems and would always have rated it 4 or 5 stars.\n\nHowever version 5.4 update caused a conflict with another plugin.\n\nWhen I raised this problem in the support forum I was given the blunt response to contact the other plugin provider for support and the author marked the problem as resolved.\n\nVery poor support attitude to try and pass the buck and forget about it.\n\nI will now be changing to Caldera Forms on dozens of websites I manage.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">V5.4 breaks recaptcha</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/bmulleckerwebtek\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/798d46b740e521c48a531122a9daa718?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/798d46b740e521c48a531122a9daa718?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/bmulleckerwebtek\" class=\"reviewer-name\">bmulleckerwebtek</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">February 26, 2021</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Fantastic plugin! BUT, the 5.4 update has an issue when using the recaptcha integration. In its current state, using rv3, forms will not submit at all, and an error is thrown in the console. In the meantime, I recommend sticking to update 5.3 to avoid this issue until a fix is in place.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">v5.4 Breaks Functionality (&quot;Spinning Wheel&quot; Problem)</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"2 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"2\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/martymcleod\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/5a9da6e9198ea556f881d16625c2f842?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/5a9da6e9198ea556f881d16625c2f842?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/martymcleod\" class=\"reviewer-name\">martymcleod</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">February 25, 2021</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Unfortunately updating to v5.4 yesterday was a mistake. The mail functionality appears to be working but I\'m getting the \"spinning wheel\" problem when clicking Submit &amp; no message is displayed - <strong>it just hangs.</strong> Site visitors won\'t know it\'s working, so I had to roll back to the previous version.\n\nPrior to 5.4 I\'ve enjoying Contact Form 7 as a very lightweight replacement for my older WP Forms contact form. In both cases, reCaptcha\'s Javascript hurts page speed so I used a work-around: I used the Quiz feature in Contact Form 7 but instead of display a text question I use a custom-made captcha image of my own. Has been working great, and no page overhead!\n\nHopefully whatever the problem with v5.4 is, it\'ll get resolved, but that\'s very disappointing. I get the feeling it wasn\'t tested. :(\n\n<em>**I\'ll be happy to update my review if it\'s resolved. Thanks.**</em></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">5.4 update breaks the use of google recaptcha shortcode</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/fluiddesk\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/395b21f56c3c773baf4b97aed985f7ae?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/395b21f56c3c773baf4b97aed985f7ae?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/fluiddesk\" class=\"reviewer-name\">fluiddesk</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">February 25, 2021</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">The latest 5.4 update allows you to use googel recaptcha shortcodes still but if the user doesn\'t tick the box you normally get a warning and a orange box stating there are missing fields ect, after this update the text is missing from the warning and only the orange border is shown.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Effective plugin</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"4 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"4\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/macadk\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/ecfacca4538d07cc3a6a106d61fd2339?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/ecfacca4538d07cc3a6a106d61fd2339?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/macadk\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Doug Nix <small>(macadk)</small></a> on <span class=\"review-date\">February 24, 2021</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I started using this plugin a few years ago based on the large number of installations claimed in the plugin repository.\n\nThe plugin has been quite reliable for me, however, the issue with the reCAPTCHA 3.0 implementation causing 100% of messages sent to land in the spam folder has not yet been resolved to my knowledge. This is a long-standing issue that needs to be addressed. The good thing is that you can implement AKISMET spam checking in the design of your forms, presuming that you have AKISMET installed on your site.\n\nOverall I\'m pretty happy with the plugin but like many other users, I\'m frustrated by the poor/absent/slow support responses.</div>\n</div>\n\";}s:13:\"download_link\";s:61:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/contact-form-7.5.4.zip\";s:11:\"screenshots\";a:1:{i:1;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:67:\"https://ps.w.org/contact-form-7/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=1176454\";s:7:\"caption\";s:16:\"screenshot-1.png\";}}s:4:\"tags\";a:5:{s:7:\"contact\";s:7:\"contact\";s:12:\"contact-form\";s:12:\"contact form\";s:5:\"email\";s:5:\"email\";s:8:\"feedback\";s:8:\"feedback\";s:4:\"form\";s:4:\"form\";}s:8:\"versions\";a:149:{s:3:\"1.1\";s:61:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/contact-form-7.1.1.zip\";s:4:\"1.10\";s:62:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/contact-form-7.1.10.zip\";s:8:\"1.10.0.1\";s:66:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/contact-form-7.1.10.0.1.zip\";s:6:\"1.10.1\";s:64:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/contact-form-7.1.10.1.zip\";s:3:\"1.2\";s:61:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/contact-form-7.1.2.zip\";s:3:\"1.3\";s:61:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/contact-form-7.1.3.zip\";s:5:\"1.3.1\";s:63:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/contact-form-7.1.3.1.zip\";s:5:\"1.3.2\";s:63:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plug